<section>
  <h2>The right question</h2>
  <p>Asking a good question does take more consideration than you would initially think. I have worked in various IT support roles where I had to both answer questions as well ask questions to other specialists. I know what it's like for both sides of the question. It is important to provide brief, yet detailed and only relevant information, while making sure you aren't omitting anything helpful. It can be important to provide environment variables when they are relevant, but they should be very succinct.</p>
  <p>When it comes to asking questions about code, I understand it is important to reduce the amount of example code to a minimum and use easy to understand, general variables and names. This is what I took away from the presented article.</p>
