<section>
  <h2>Asking in person</h2>
  <p>When I approached colleagues with questions I always made sure I had all information ready, either jotted down on paper or by bringing a laptop or making sure we can look at the same screen quickly.</p>
  <p>What is emphasized is that the person providing help is taking out time and that is very true. It is goodwill and I make sure to let the other person know it is appreciated. Likewise, I am always happy to help someone who is prepared and whom I know will be helped on their with the provided information. I just believe that we can pass on what we are given. I think that is our natural inclination and I like to accommodate that.</p>
</section>

